1
00:00:00,360 --> 00:00:05,360
(This series is a work of fiction inspired
by questions that arise within the human heart.)

2
00:00:05,380 --> 00:00:09,760
(It is not intended to offend or pass judgment
on any beliefs, religions, or individuals.)

3
00:00:10,118 --> 00:00:12,290
(Previous Chapter)
Kongkit was wrong for starting it,

4
00:00:12,631 --> 00:00:14,530
but you two were at fault too.

5
00:00:14,848 --> 00:00:16,568
The only wrong thing you did
was to help me,

6
00:00:16,597 --> 00:00:17,985
and now you're screwed too.

7
00:00:18,797 --> 00:00:20,210
Don't help me next time.

8
00:00:20,454 --> 00:00:22,530
I don't have any friends.

9
00:00:23,150 --> 00:00:24,401
You're the only one I know.

10
00:00:24,720 --> 00:00:29,112
Lust means letting desire control us.

11
00:00:29,740 --> 00:00:31,096
Wanna sneak out for some roti?

12
00:00:32,247 --> 00:00:33,451
You really won't come?

13
00:00:33,964 --> 00:00:35,900
Come on. I'll help you up.

14
00:00:36,783 --> 00:00:39,026
What if you can't stop it?

15
00:00:40,028 --> 00:00:41,090
Then you fight it.

16
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:51,060
THE SEVEN DEADLY SINS:

17
00:00:51,080 --> 00:00:54,580
PRIDE, GREED, LUST, WRATH,
GLUTTONY, ENVY, SLOTH

18
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:57,850
LUST

19
00:01:20,829 --> 00:01:21,829
Tan.

20
00:01:23,897 --> 00:01:24,897
Tan!

21
00:01:27,158 --> 00:01:28,158
What?

22
00:01:28,402 --> 00:01:30,610
For New Year's break,
are you coming to my home?

23
00:01:30,808 --> 00:01:32,382
I'll write to my mom,

24
00:01:32,590 --> 00:01:34,204
so she can ask Father for permission.

25
00:01:36,628 --> 00:01:38,377
Can I… let you know later?

26
00:01:41,477 --> 00:01:42,477
Okay.

27
00:02:20,333 --> 00:02:21,333
Ahem.

28
00:02:22,611 --> 00:02:27,010
It's been… ten minutes
since my last confession.

29
00:02:32,770 --> 00:02:33,800
You're such a tease.

30
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:38,647
For me, it's been a long time
since my last confession.

31
00:02:39,580 --> 00:02:42,970
So long I can't even remember.

32
00:02:45,930 --> 00:02:47,560
Then shouldn't you confess?

33
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,699
God wouldn't listen to me anyway.

34
00:02:57,204 --> 00:02:58,297
But you?

35
00:02:59,497 --> 00:03:01,202
What sins would you even have to confess?

36
00:03:31,277 --> 00:03:33,801
The Gospel today is about repentance.

37
00:03:34,810 --> 00:03:39,600
But in God's eyes, repentance
doesn't mean He will punish us.

38
00:03:39,945 --> 00:03:43,900
It means He's waiting for us to come home.

39
00:03:45,750 --> 00:03:47,499
We've all lost our way.

40
00:03:48,685 --> 00:03:50,299
Lost because of ignorance.

41
00:03:51,444 --> 00:03:53,401
Lost because of weakness.

42
00:03:54,448 --> 00:04:00,250
And sometimes, we got lost
because we thought it was love.

43
00:04:02,460 --> 00:04:04,198
<i>Humans long for love</i>

44
00:04:04,791 --> 00:04:07,801
<i>because God made us with His love.</i>

45
00:04:08,573 --> 00:04:12,600
<i>Scripture says God is love.</i>

46
00:04:14,130 --> 00:04:15,971
<i>When a human heart starts to beat,</i>

47
00:04:17,017 --> 00:04:19,902
<i>it naturally begins to search for love.</i>

48
00:04:21,580 --> 00:04:23,300
But the question is,

49
00:04:23,820 --> 00:04:28,204
<i>does every kind of love
lead us closer to Him?</i>

50
00:04:31,933 --> 00:04:32,933
Father.

51
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:34,440
Yes?

52
00:04:34,890 --> 00:04:40,600
If some feelings make you feel bad,

53
00:04:41,870 --> 00:04:43,397
is that wrong, Father?

54
00:04:44,368 --> 00:04:45,897
Sometimes it isn't wrong.

55
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:49,699
But it makes you afraid.

56
00:04:50,960 --> 00:04:52,400
Afraid you'll do wrong.

57
00:04:54,571 --> 00:04:55,597
Fear…

58
00:04:58,262 --> 00:05:00,210
How do you deal with it?

59
00:05:02,380 --> 00:05:03,939
When you're afraid,

60
00:05:04,410 --> 00:05:07,048
do you run from it or stay with it?

61
00:05:09,173 --> 00:05:10,600
What if I still don't know?

62
00:05:15,025 --> 00:05:16,401
It's okay not to know.

63
00:05:17,133 --> 00:05:21,096
God isn't in a rush
to get an answer from us.

64
00:05:23,466 --> 00:05:25,395
<i>Having feelings isn't a sin.</i>

65
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:28,602
<i>The struggle of coping with them</i>

66
00:05:29,161 --> 00:05:32,202
<i>is what proves our faithfulness to God.</i>

67
00:05:32,770 --> 00:05:36,902
<i>So don't be afraid to come back to God.</i>

68
00:05:38,552 --> 00:05:40,320
<i>No matter what happens,</i>

69
00:05:41,090 --> 00:05:42,499
don't run from God.

70
00:05:43,570 --> 00:05:46,401
God always understands us.

71
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:09,900
"Ticket to Heaven"
(Episode 3)

72
00:07:25,376 --> 00:07:26,376
Tan.

73
00:07:28,118 --> 00:07:29,118
What's up?

74
00:07:29,620 --> 00:07:30,900
You're totally spacing out.

75
00:07:33,442 --> 00:07:34,496
Lots of homework.

76
00:07:37,274 --> 00:07:39,198
Come on, what's wrong?

77
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:41,360
Tell me.

78
00:07:43,408 --> 00:07:44,447
I'm fine.

79
00:07:52,020 --> 00:07:54,600
Fine, then.

80
00:07:54,780 --> 00:07:55,780
Barth,

81
00:07:57,011 --> 00:07:58,198
that's my textbook.

82
00:08:24,300 --> 00:08:25,300
How about this?

83
00:08:26,170 --> 00:08:27,302
Play a game with me.

84
00:08:28,543 --> 00:08:30,700
If you win, I'll stop bugging you.

85
00:08:33,370 --> 00:08:34,497
You better mean that.

86
00:09:05,546 --> 00:09:06,546
I won.

87
00:09:08,680 --> 00:09:09,728
I won.

88
00:09:14,743 --> 00:09:16,010
Guess you have to tell me now.

89
00:09:16,330 --> 00:09:19,930
Tell me right now.

90
00:09:36,290 --> 00:09:38,617
Come on, Ta! Come on!

91
00:09:38,640 --> 00:09:39,802
Go, go, go!

92
00:09:41,847 --> 00:09:43,731
Yeah! Yeah!

93
00:09:44,510 --> 00:09:45,510
That's how it's done!

94
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:55,100
Yay! Woo!

95
00:10:04,072 --> 00:10:05,432
All right, take a break, everyone.

96
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:08,897
A kind parent treated all of us today.

97
00:10:10,582 --> 00:10:13,001
Come on. Hand these out.

98
00:10:14,630 --> 00:10:16,276
- Come on, hurry.
- Which color do you want?

99
00:10:16,300 --> 00:10:18,099
Go on.

100
00:10:18,310 --> 00:10:19,310
Come on, hurry.

101
00:10:21,983 --> 00:10:23,397
No fighting over them.

102
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:39,801
- Kong.
- Yeah?

103
00:10:39,933 --> 00:10:40,933
Look.

104
00:11:03,536 --> 00:11:05,798
All right, everyone. Time's up.

105
00:11:07,150 --> 00:11:08,503
Come on. Let's go.

106
00:11:08,777 --> 00:11:10,503
Go shower and get ready for dinner.

107
00:11:11,054 --> 00:11:12,094
Come on, give me the ball.

108
00:11:12,223 --> 00:11:14,475
Kong, did you see my last shot?

109
00:11:14,506 --> 00:11:15,312
I was like Beckham.

110
00:11:15,333 --> 00:11:16,890
Wow. You're such a show-off, Ryu.

111
00:11:18,130 --> 00:11:18,790
That last shot.

112
00:11:18,819 --> 00:11:21,702
I thought you slipped
and the ball just happened to go in.

113
00:11:22,220 --> 00:11:23,930
One more and I'd have had a hat trick.

114
00:11:27,308 --> 00:11:29,980
Hey, Kong. You guys go ahead.

115
00:11:30,059 --> 00:11:31,059
I'll catch up.

116
00:11:32,151 --> 00:11:33,151
Okay.

117
00:11:51,075 --> 00:11:52,302
They're all gone.

118
00:11:54,401 --> 00:11:55,841
I was looking forward to having one.

119
00:12:01,180 --> 00:12:02,180
Hey,

120
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:04,398
did you save this for me?

121
00:12:06,179 --> 00:12:07,179
Thanks a lot.

122
00:12:45,863 --> 00:12:46,863
Why?

123
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:48,440
What is it, Tanrak?

124
00:12:50,010 --> 00:12:51,364
Why are you covering your nose?

125
00:12:53,306 --> 00:12:54,306
Huh?

126
00:12:54,697 --> 00:12:55,800
Do I stink?

127
00:12:56,322 --> 00:12:57,322
I stink, right?

128
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:00,933
People sweat when they play football.

129
00:13:00,954 --> 00:13:02,597
Sweat stinks. So what?

130
00:13:04,630 --> 00:13:06,352
Sweat stinks, right?

131
00:13:06,990 --> 00:13:08,099
Let me wipe it on you.

132
00:13:09,940 --> 00:13:11,257
Come on. Just a little.

133
00:13:11,977 --> 00:13:12,977
Come on.

134
00:13:15,934 --> 00:13:16,934
What are you do–ow!

135
00:13:19,398 --> 00:13:20,398
Tanrak!

136
00:13:23,016 --> 00:13:24,016
Stop.

137
00:13:24,051 --> 00:13:25,051
Come here.

138
00:13:26,430 --> 00:13:28,545
It's common to get sweaty
when you play football.

139
00:13:28,859 --> 00:13:29,859
Let me wipe it on you.

140
00:13:53,385 --> 00:13:54,600
Help, please! Help!

141
00:13:56,229 --> 00:13:57,229
Tan.

142
00:14:02,310 --> 00:14:04,350
What did Master ask us to carry?
It's so damn heavy.

143
00:14:04,730 --> 00:14:05,730
Where do we put this?

144
00:14:06,420 --> 00:14:07,420
How do we set it up?

145
00:14:07,653 --> 00:14:09,097
Maybe you…

146
00:14:09,816 --> 00:14:12,299
leave some space
for people to walk through.

147
00:14:13,105 --> 00:14:14,253
Move it a bit more.

148
00:14:14,638 --> 00:14:15,638
Kong.

149
00:14:16,357 --> 00:14:18,303
Then set that side up evenly.

150
00:14:19,204 --> 00:14:20,604
Can I get some help over here?

151
00:14:21,077 --> 00:14:22,077
Yes, Master.

152
00:14:28,228 --> 00:14:29,228
Alright.

153
00:14:29,282 --> 00:14:32,198
Take these and line them up over there.

154
00:14:32,250 --> 00:14:34,428
Everyone else,
once you're done setting up,

155
00:14:34,453 --> 00:14:36,402
sit with your vocal sections.

156
00:14:36,746 --> 00:14:37,746
Go on.

157
00:14:43,250 --> 00:14:44,900
Sit with your section.

158
00:14:45,348 --> 00:14:48,201
Today, we have students
from several schools here.

159
00:14:48,470 --> 00:14:52,500
You're all members of our church choir.

160
00:14:53,010 --> 00:14:55,602
So welcome, everyone.
Some of you may have never met before.

161
00:14:56,081 --> 00:14:57,081
Wait.

162
00:14:57,823 --> 00:14:59,502
Where's Nat?

163
00:15:00,510 --> 00:15:01,510
I'm not sure, Master.

164
00:15:02,038 --> 00:15:03,998
Kongdech, you sing bass for him today.

165
00:15:04,487 --> 00:15:05,201
Yes, Master.

166
00:15:05,456 --> 00:15:06,456
Barth.

167
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:08,195
Let's check your vocal range.

168
00:15:10,779 --> 00:15:11,779
Come on.

169
00:15:11,870 --> 00:15:13,296
Everyone, give Barth a hand.

170
00:15:13,571 --> 00:15:15,151
That's it.

171
00:15:16,191 --> 00:15:18,103
Let's welcome our new member.

172
00:15:18,604 --> 00:15:22,010
All right, tenor.
The highest note you'll probably sing is…

173
00:15:22,253 --> 00:15:25,761
Ha, ha, ha, ha, ha.

174
00:15:25,828 --> 00:15:26,828
This one.

175
00:15:27,040 --> 00:15:28,040
Go on.

176
00:15:29,303 --> 00:15:30,303
Ha…

177
00:15:31,884 --> 00:15:32,884
Ha…

178
00:15:33,482 --> 00:15:35,000
Ha…

179
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:36,474
- Ha…
- Ha…

180
00:15:36,580 --> 00:15:38,000
- Ha…
- Ha…

181
00:15:38,251 --> 00:15:39,401
Ha…

182
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:44,703
A bit more. Full voice.

183
00:15:45,118 --> 00:15:46,202
Haaa.

184
00:15:47,915 --> 00:15:48,915
Haaaaa.

185
00:15:51,456 --> 00:15:52,494
You can do it.

186
00:15:52,580 --> 00:15:54,102
Okay. Tenor it is.

187
00:15:56,491 --> 00:15:57,202
All good?

188
00:15:57,287 --> 00:15:58,299
We're missing one set.

189
00:15:58,330 --> 00:15:59,096
One more set?

190
00:15:59,306 --> 00:16:01,000
Tanrak. Can I have one set?

191
00:16:02,281 --> 00:16:03,130
Take mine.

192
00:16:03,207 --> 00:16:04,536
No, it's okay. I'll get it myself.

193
00:16:04,560 --> 00:16:05,604
Hey, take mine.

194
00:16:06,050 --> 00:16:06,702
Oh!

195
00:16:06,882 --> 00:16:07,497
Whoa!

196
00:16:07,522 --> 00:16:09,100
Shit, sorry.

197
00:16:14,739 --> 00:16:16,300
Oh, take Cherry to the bathroom.

198
00:16:16,970 --> 00:16:19,805
And you two, go get a mop.

199
00:16:19,885 --> 00:16:20,885
Yes, Master.

200
00:16:27,580 --> 00:16:28,703
Bring the mop over.

201
00:16:29,379 --> 00:16:33,290
Once you're done eating,
please help clean up.

202
00:16:34,878 --> 00:16:37,903
Let's decide what songs we'll sing.

203
00:16:38,204 --> 00:16:39,700
Whoa. There they are.

204
00:16:41,872 --> 00:16:42,872
Tan, look.

205
00:16:45,220 --> 00:16:46,234
Wow!

206
00:16:46,250 --> 00:16:48,010
That's our Christmas play couple
right there.

207
00:16:48,260 --> 00:16:50,302
Joseph and the Virgin Mary.

208
00:16:51,117 --> 00:16:52,202
What are you talking about?

209
00:16:52,468 --> 00:16:53,802
Exactly, Kongdech.

210
00:16:54,164 --> 00:16:56,497
Before you tease them,
ask if they even want to do it.

211
00:16:56,962 --> 00:16:58,000
Come on, Master.

212
00:16:58,130 --> 00:16:59,600
I play Joseph every year.

213
00:16:59,807 --> 00:17:01,173
Let Barth do it this year.

214
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:04,401
What do you say, Barth?

215
00:17:04,663 --> 00:17:05,663
Interested?

216
00:17:07,531 --> 00:17:08,610
What do you say, Tan?

217
00:17:11,565 --> 00:17:12,829
It's okay. You can tell me later.

218
00:17:12,853 --> 00:17:14,103
Go on. Take a seat.

219
00:17:15,582 --> 00:17:17,299
Give me some more song suggestions.

220
00:17:17,788 --> 00:17:19,102
Jingle Bells.

221
00:17:23,497 --> 00:17:24,602
Two more songs, please.

222
00:17:25,216 --> 00:17:26,600
Joy to the World.

223
00:17:47,078 --> 00:17:48,100
Thanks, Barth.

224
00:17:48,868 --> 00:17:50,650
Master Win lent me a shirt.

225
00:17:51,386 --> 00:17:53,700
Should I wash this and return it?

226
00:17:54,585 --> 00:17:55,900
No need.

227
00:17:57,442 --> 00:17:58,158
Uh…

228
00:17:58,232 --> 00:17:59,297
Sorry again.

229
00:17:59,500 --> 00:18:00,500
It's okay.

230
00:18:01,040 --> 00:18:02,900
I'll leave this shirt

231
00:18:03,548 --> 00:18:06,610
with Master Win
and have him return it to you.

232
00:18:06,721 --> 00:18:07,721
Okay.

233
00:18:09,010 --> 00:18:10,010
See you.

234
00:18:10,096 --> 00:18:11,401
Let's go. It's getting late.

235
00:18:12,040 --> 00:18:13,040
Tanrak.

236
00:18:32,736 --> 00:18:33,804
Don't rush back yet.

237
00:18:34,986 --> 00:18:35,986
Huh?

238
00:18:37,660 --> 00:18:39,800
We didn't get to eat anything earlier,
did we?

239
00:18:40,917 --> 00:18:41,917
No.

240
00:18:42,470 --> 00:18:43,798
I'll take you to the market.

241
00:18:46,110 --> 00:18:48,302
What? I'm not going.

242
00:18:48,651 --> 00:18:49,651
Come on.

243
00:18:54,386 --> 00:18:55,386
Hey, Kong.

244
00:18:55,779 --> 00:18:57,801
You go ahead.

245
00:18:57,911 --> 00:18:58,952
I'm going to the bathroom first.

246
00:18:58,976 --> 00:19:00,400
Yeah, okay.

247
00:19:29,106 --> 00:19:30,700
Ready? Let's go.

248
00:19:47,173 --> 00:19:48,802
Oh, Tanrak!

249
00:19:53,202 --> 00:19:54,330
What are you doing out here?

250
00:19:57,912 --> 00:19:59,096
I…

251
00:20:00,040 --> 00:20:01,810
We ran out of donuts.

252
00:20:02,869 --> 00:20:06,220
So Master asked me to order more
for the choir club.

253
00:20:06,245 --> 00:20:07,397
I see.

254
00:20:07,828 --> 00:20:08,828
Hmm.

255
00:20:09,448 --> 00:20:11,204
I don't think I have enough left.

256
00:20:13,571 --> 00:20:14,571
What about these?

257
00:20:14,659 --> 00:20:15,770
These are already reserved.

258
00:20:15,791 --> 00:20:18,302
I have to deliver them
to a wedding early tomorrow.

259
00:20:20,139 --> 00:20:22,650
I'll have to box them first
to see if there are any left.

260
00:20:25,102 --> 00:20:26,401
Never mind then.

261
00:20:27,508 --> 00:20:28,254
Well,

262
00:20:28,281 --> 00:20:30,522
- Never mind. I…
- I can help box them up.

263
00:20:33,874 --> 00:20:35,980
It might make things faster.

264
00:20:38,040 --> 00:20:39,320
And maybe there'll be some left.

265
00:20:40,155 --> 00:20:41,155
Well…

266
00:20:41,562 --> 00:20:42,167
Good.

267
00:20:42,195 --> 00:20:45,210
That would help. Come this way.

268
00:20:45,408 --> 00:20:46,408
Come on.

269
00:20:47,881 --> 00:20:49,398
What's your name?

270
00:20:50,134 --> 00:20:51,134
Barth.

271
00:20:55,742 --> 00:20:57,299
I brought you some more.

272
00:20:58,444 --> 00:20:59,700
You don't need this one.

273
00:21:00,308 --> 00:21:01,397
Thank you so much.

274
00:21:08,197 --> 00:21:09,197
Hey.

275
00:21:09,620 --> 00:21:11,598
If we sneak one,
do you think she'll notice?

276
00:21:13,050 --> 00:21:14,050
Hey.

277
00:21:55,035 --> 00:21:57,400
Close the door
and help me clean the kitchen.

278
00:22:02,084 --> 00:22:02,955
Sorry, boys.

279
00:22:02,985 --> 00:22:04,700
I didn't make extra dough.

280
00:22:05,271 --> 00:22:05,982
Here.

281
00:22:06,010 --> 00:22:07,402
There really is only one left.

282
00:22:07,611 --> 00:22:08,611
Oh.

283
00:22:09,668 --> 00:22:11,980
- Please take this to share.
- Thank you so much.

284
00:22:13,300 --> 00:22:14,200
Get back safely.

285
00:22:14,290 --> 00:22:15,290
Yes, ma'am.

286
00:22:26,635 --> 00:22:27,635
Here.

287
00:22:28,152 --> 00:22:29,401
Our pay for today.

288
00:22:46,265 --> 00:22:47,265
Here.

289
00:22:48,320 --> 00:22:49,500
We worked hard together.

290
00:22:49,590 --> 00:22:50,699
So we should eat together.

291
00:22:57,170 --> 00:22:58,170
Thanks.

292
00:23:04,631 --> 00:23:05,631
Mm.

293
00:23:09,080 --> 00:23:10,200
It's pretty yummy, right?

294
00:23:11,448 --> 00:23:13,010
But it's so damn dry.

295
00:23:16,881 --> 00:23:17,881
Yeah, it is.

296
00:23:29,767 --> 00:23:30,767
What?

297
00:23:35,210 --> 00:23:36,210
Nothing.

298
00:23:37,287 --> 00:23:38,500
I just…

299
00:23:39,590 --> 00:23:41,000
haven't seen you smile in a while.

300
00:23:46,114 --> 00:23:47,114
Really?

301
00:23:51,480 --> 00:23:53,320
I thought you were mad at me or something.

302
00:23:59,746 --> 00:24:00,746
It's nothing.

303
00:24:08,930 --> 00:24:10,696
If I did anything to upset you,

304
00:24:12,315 --> 00:24:13,410
I'm sorry.

305
00:24:19,755 --> 00:24:20,903
Don't worry about it.

306
00:24:26,755 --> 00:24:27,755
How can I not?

307
00:24:28,219 --> 00:24:29,980
How am I not supposed to worry about it?

308
00:24:30,920 --> 00:24:33,893
You know I don't have many friends.

309
00:24:37,340 --> 00:24:38,700
In all of Magdalene House,

310
00:24:39,308 --> 00:24:41,303
you're the only one
I can talk to about anything.

311
00:24:42,480 --> 00:24:44,148
And I feel comfortable around you.

312
00:24:51,297 --> 00:24:52,297
Same here.

313
00:24:57,623 --> 00:24:58,623
Really?

314
00:25:07,480 --> 00:25:08,800
Can you promise me?

315
00:25:10,780 --> 00:25:11,780
From now on,

316
00:25:12,380 --> 00:25:14,100
if something's wrong,
just tell me straight.

317
00:25:28,960 --> 00:25:29,960
Ahem.

318
00:25:32,739 --> 00:25:34,897
This is my body which is given for you.

319
00:25:43,140 --> 00:25:44,140
Barth.

320
00:25:44,490 --> 00:25:45,697
That's not funny.

321
00:25:46,712 --> 00:25:49,299
God is so going to punish you.

322
00:25:56,143 --> 00:25:57,143
I'm not scared.

323
00:25:58,139 --> 00:25:59,819
A guy like me
isn't going to heaven anyway.

324
00:26:02,110 --> 00:26:03,110
I'm just practicing.

325
00:26:03,493 --> 00:26:06,595
Maybe one day I'll get to say Mass.

326
00:26:08,114 --> 00:26:09,114
I'll be ready.

327
00:26:10,339 --> 00:26:11,982
Yes, Father Bodin.

328
00:26:13,717 --> 00:26:14,717
Wow.

329
00:26:16,570 --> 00:26:17,703
Nope.

330
00:26:18,238 --> 00:26:21,574
I really can't picture you like that.

331
00:26:23,986 --> 00:26:24,986
Why?

332
00:26:26,400 --> 00:26:28,099
Don't I look like I could be a priest?

333
00:26:42,002 --> 00:26:43,002
Cheers.

334
00:26:55,590 --> 00:26:56,896
My source tells me

335
00:26:57,580 --> 00:26:59,299
you got Cherry's pager number.

336
00:27:00,795 --> 00:27:02,200
What pager? That's bullshit.

337
00:27:04,014 --> 00:27:05,500
My source also tells me

338
00:27:06,940 --> 00:27:09,300
Cherry doesn't have a boyfriend.

339
00:27:10,930 --> 00:27:13,002
Wrong again. She totally has a boyfriend.

340
00:27:15,760 --> 00:27:17,503
So you did look into it, didn't you?

341
00:27:19,792 --> 00:27:20,912
You better keep this buried.

342
00:27:21,315 --> 00:27:24,490
If Master Phak finds out,
Father Arnon will hear about it for sure.

343
00:27:33,914 --> 00:27:35,401
Is the pager story true?

344
00:27:37,545 --> 00:27:38,545
Barth!

345
00:27:41,382 --> 00:27:43,179
Whoa, Barth. You're so cool.

346
00:27:47,140 --> 00:27:48,140
Behave yourself.

347
00:27:48,300 --> 00:27:49,899
We are still in Magdalene House.

348
00:28:00,684 --> 00:28:01,696
Oh, Tan.

349
00:28:02,620 --> 00:28:04,180
Aren't you going to go to your friends?

350
00:28:04,706 --> 00:28:05,706
Well.

351
00:28:05,862 --> 00:28:06,862
They…

352
00:28:07,271 --> 00:28:08,497
didn't come to see me.

353
00:28:26,005 --> 00:28:27,005
Tanrak.

354
00:28:29,042 --> 00:28:30,198
Dip it in red for me.

355
00:28:33,160 --> 00:28:34,302
Hey, Ryu.

356
00:28:34,481 --> 00:28:36,499
- What's up?
- Help Barth out.

357
00:28:37,150 --> 00:28:37,905
Sure.

358
00:28:37,930 --> 00:28:38,930
Easy-peasy.

359
00:28:48,693 --> 00:28:49,700
Hold the ladder for me.

360
00:28:53,380 --> 00:28:54,503
Hey, hey, Barth.

361
00:28:55,337 --> 00:28:56,604
I saw it this evening.

362
00:28:57,133 --> 00:28:58,133
Saw what?

363
00:28:59,284 --> 00:29:00,600
Cherry.

364
00:29:01,530 --> 00:29:02,619
You haven't been here long,

365
00:29:03,080 --> 00:29:05,401
but you're certainly the coolest now.

366
00:29:10,590 --> 00:29:12,453
- Is your hair color cool enough?
- Ow, shit!

367
00:29:13,022 --> 00:29:14,022
Barth!

368
00:29:15,324 --> 00:29:16,324
What the hell?

369
00:29:17,120 --> 00:29:18,720
Tan, come hold the ladder instead.

370
00:29:18,850 --> 00:29:19,951
I'm going to wash my hair.

371
00:29:20,355 --> 00:29:21,580
What the hell?

372
00:29:31,170 --> 00:29:32,170
Hey.

373
00:29:33,354 --> 00:29:34,493
Hold the ladder for me.

374
00:29:35,980 --> 00:29:38,099
Hold it. This is dangerous.

375
00:29:55,308 --> 00:29:56,308
What?

376
00:29:57,490 --> 00:29:58,497
Hey, you got it on me.

377
00:30:00,284 --> 00:30:02,302
Only a little bit.

378
00:30:07,463 --> 00:30:08,602
Come on. I'm not playing.

379
00:30:09,040 --> 00:30:11,000
Hurry up, so we'll have time
to do something else.

380
00:30:21,546 --> 00:30:22,546
Done.

381
00:30:35,910 --> 00:30:36,910
Tan.

382
00:30:37,550 --> 00:30:40,102
Do you think Barth likes Cherry?

383
00:30:42,420 --> 00:30:43,700
How would I know?

384
00:30:44,272 --> 00:30:45,339
But for me,

385
00:30:45,370 --> 00:30:47,982
I don't know if Barth likes her,

386
00:30:48,011 --> 00:30:50,250
but Cherry definitely likes Barth.

387
00:30:54,047 --> 00:30:55,047
Really?

388
00:30:55,444 --> 00:30:56,650
What makes you think that?

389
00:30:57,190 --> 00:30:59,045
Come on, think about it.

390
00:30:59,480 --> 00:31:00,617
If she wasn't into him,

391
00:31:00,912 --> 00:31:02,480
would she come all the way to school?

392
00:31:02,657 --> 00:31:04,601
Yeah. Ryu just told me.

393
00:31:05,277 --> 00:31:07,099
I saw it with my own eyes.

394
00:31:07,247 --> 00:31:09,930
- For real?
- Barth definitely likes Cherry first.

395
00:31:10,780 --> 00:31:13,697
I think, at any rate,
Cherry must like Barth.

396
00:31:13,720 --> 00:31:15,699
But whether Barth likes Cherry…

397
00:31:16,074 --> 00:31:17,650
Barth is such a flirt.

398
00:31:17,674 --> 00:31:20,373
I think Cherry definitely likes Barth.

399
00:31:20,460 --> 00:31:22,096
- Barth likes her first.
- You can tell from her eyes.

400
00:31:22,120 --> 00:31:24,699
And Barth's eyes when he talked to her?
I mean…

401
00:31:42,600 --> 00:31:43,600
What's wrong?

402
00:31:44,552 --> 00:31:46,398
Hurry up. I need to do my homework.

403
00:31:52,780 --> 00:31:53,780
What's wrong?

404
00:32:00,685 --> 00:32:01,685
Tanrak.

405
00:32:02,580 --> 00:32:03,645
Hurry. It's getting late.

406
00:32:03,675 --> 00:32:05,902
There are mosquitoes everywhere.

407
00:32:06,910 --> 00:32:07,910
They're biting me.

408
00:32:18,834 --> 00:32:19,834
What mosquitoes?

409
00:32:21,499 --> 00:32:22,499
Hey!

410
00:32:23,681 --> 00:32:24,700
Where are they?

411
00:32:25,500 --> 00:32:26,819
Barth, it's getting everywhere.

412
00:32:28,059 --> 00:32:29,600
This helps keep mosquitoes away.

413
00:32:32,105 --> 00:32:33,337
See? There are so many around here.

414
00:32:33,361 --> 00:32:34,361
Barth.

415
00:32:36,120 --> 00:32:37,897
What if you get bitten
and it leaves a mark?

416
00:32:44,300 --> 00:32:45,998
If you're not helping, go away.

417
00:32:48,140 --> 00:32:49,702
I am helping
by keeping mosquitoes away.

418
00:32:55,678 --> 00:32:56,678
Fine. I'll help.

419
00:33:23,684 --> 00:33:24,684
Tanrak.

420
00:33:25,391 --> 00:33:26,391
Mm.

421
00:33:27,899 --> 00:33:28,899
What is it?

422
00:33:30,598 --> 00:33:31,598
Are you asleep?

423
00:33:33,213 --> 00:33:34,299
I need to talk to you.

424
00:33:42,305 --> 00:33:43,305
About Cherry.

425
00:33:58,637 --> 00:33:59,637
Well…

426
00:34:00,831 --> 00:34:02,810
Cherry asked me
to be in the Christmas play.

427
00:34:06,930 --> 00:34:07,930
So…

428
00:34:08,348 --> 00:34:09,348
it's up to you.

429
00:34:09,798 --> 00:34:10,798
Decide for yourself.

430
00:34:19,974 --> 00:34:21,586
I'm asking you because

431
00:34:23,008 --> 00:34:24,008
well…

432
00:34:25,560 --> 00:34:27,400
if you don't want me to do it, I won't.

433
00:34:30,208 --> 00:34:31,610
What does it have to do with me?

434
00:34:33,890 --> 00:34:34,890
It does.

435
00:34:36,668 --> 00:34:38,001
I want you to be okay with it.

436
00:34:46,250 --> 00:34:47,250
Tanrak.

437
00:34:48,488 --> 00:34:49,488
What do you say?

438
00:34:56,650 --> 00:34:57,650
Huh?

439
00:34:58,598 --> 00:34:59,290
Huh?

440
00:34:59,502 --> 00:35:00,502
What do you say?

441
00:35:02,094 --> 00:35:03,094
Well…

442
00:35:03,408 --> 00:35:04,408
just do it.

443
00:35:05,592 --> 00:35:07,297
Christmas only comes once a year.

444
00:35:26,820 --> 00:35:28,402
What's wrong with you? Hm?

445
00:35:29,617 --> 00:35:31,450
Didn't we say we'd be honest
with each other?

446
00:35:32,419 --> 00:35:33,419
Hm?

447
00:35:35,078 --> 00:35:36,097
Nothing's wrong.

448
00:35:37,137 --> 00:35:38,137
Really.

449
00:35:39,230 --> 00:35:41,002
Then act normal already.

450
00:35:44,342 --> 00:35:45,342
Come on.

451
00:35:49,814 --> 00:35:50,459
Hm?

452
00:35:50,617 --> 00:35:51,617
Hmm.

453
00:35:54,429 --> 00:35:56,250
See? This is normal.

454
00:36:02,731 --> 00:36:04,400
Don't read too much into it, okay?

455
00:36:25,971 --> 00:36:26,971
What's this?

456
00:36:31,080 --> 00:36:33,804
“Tired from football?
I'm cheering you on, Ryu. From Eve.”

457
00:36:35,134 --> 00:36:36,134
Is there more?

458
00:36:37,183 --> 00:36:39,997
“I love hearing you sing ‘Season Change.'”

459
00:36:41,047 --> 00:36:42,497
You're so cool, Ryu.

460
00:36:42,888 --> 00:36:46,097
Hey, hey, hey. You guys better be careful.

461
00:36:46,346 --> 00:36:47,346
If Master finds out,

462
00:36:47,469 --> 00:36:48,490
you'll be in trouble.

463
00:36:48,594 --> 00:36:49,594
I'm not scared.

464
00:36:49,666 --> 00:36:50,377
What about you, Kong?

465
00:36:50,402 --> 00:36:52,597
I saw Oh, Cherry's friend,
giving you a big smile.

466
00:36:53,219 --> 00:36:54,697
What smile? You're making stuff up.

467
00:36:55,490 --> 00:36:56,811
I'll go tell Master first, then.

468
00:36:56,840 --> 00:36:58,139
Hey, Kong. Sorry.

469
00:36:58,170 --> 00:36:59,296
Calm down. I was kidding.

470
00:36:59,600 --> 00:37:01,900
You guys need to behave.

471
00:37:02,299 --> 00:37:04,124
People already think
scholarship boys are all flirts.

472
00:37:04,148 --> 00:37:05,601
I'm getting dragged into it too.

473
00:37:05,985 --> 00:37:06,985
Can't help it.

474
00:37:07,145 --> 00:37:08,145
I'm just that cool.

475
00:37:08,528 --> 00:37:10,358
Wow. So cool.

476
00:37:10,543 --> 00:37:11,939
Kong, deal with this cool guy.

477
00:37:11,962 --> 00:37:12,962
Hey, Kong!

478
00:37:13,797 --> 00:37:14,933
How's that, cool guy?

479
00:37:15,395 --> 00:37:16,503
Where's the cool guy?

480
00:37:16,960 --> 00:37:17,960
Don't!

481
00:37:18,453 --> 00:37:19,484
So cool, right?

482
00:37:19,511 --> 00:37:20,106
Don't!

483
00:37:20,454 --> 00:37:21,571
Hey, hey!

484
00:37:22,850 --> 00:37:23,980
What are you doing?

485
00:37:24,093 --> 00:37:25,299
You're making so much noise.

486
00:37:25,651 --> 00:37:26,651
Nothing.

487
00:37:26,740 --> 00:37:28,201
The boys are just playing around.

488
00:37:29,762 --> 00:37:30,180
Go on.

489
00:37:30,200 --> 00:37:31,801
Get back to whatever you need to do.

490
00:37:33,447 --> 00:37:34,447
Oh, Tanrak.

491
00:37:34,677 --> 00:37:36,285
I need to go to the church
for a rehearsal.

492
00:37:36,309 --> 00:37:37,309
They are waiting.

493
00:37:38,105 --> 00:37:39,105
Sure.

494
00:37:41,696 --> 00:37:42,400
And…

495
00:37:42,560 --> 00:37:43,602
where's Barth?

496
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:46,810
Ms. Ying asked him
to fix a computer in the teachers' room.

497
00:37:47,451 --> 00:37:48,099
Okay.

498
00:37:48,226 --> 00:37:50,170
When he's done, tell him to hurry over.

499
00:37:51,151 --> 00:37:51,896
I'll go first.

500
00:37:51,931 --> 00:37:52,456
Alright.

501
00:37:52,482 --> 00:37:53,482
See you.

502
00:37:57,154 --> 00:37:58,154
Tan.

503
00:37:59,466 --> 00:38:00,466
Tanrak.

504
00:38:03,801 --> 00:38:04,801
Wait up.

505
00:38:06,961 --> 00:38:08,096
What took you so long?

506
00:38:08,348 --> 00:38:09,897
And where did you get that bike?

507
00:38:10,192 --> 00:38:11,597
Just get on. Hurry.

508
00:38:12,500 --> 00:38:13,902
If we're late, we'll get scolded.

509
00:38:19,256 --> 00:38:20,256
Hold on.

510
00:38:22,360 --> 00:38:23,360
Whoa!

511
00:38:24,081 --> 00:38:25,081
Can you ride?

512
00:38:27,030 --> 00:38:28,030
Give me a push.

513
00:38:35,718 --> 00:38:36,718
Go.

514
00:38:40,102 --> 00:38:41,900
I was fine walking.

515
00:38:42,841 --> 00:38:44,097
This might be even slower.

516
00:38:48,075 --> 00:38:49,075
Hold on tight.

517
00:38:53,234 --> 00:38:54,634
You know you complain a lot, right?

518
00:39:06,448 --> 00:39:07,760
You're pretty heavy too.

519
00:39:28,810 --> 00:39:30,850
I can't tell if that was faster or slower.

520
00:39:34,736 --> 00:39:35,974
You complain so much.

521
00:39:36,630 --> 00:39:38,900
Hurry up or Master Phak will yell at you.

522
00:39:39,936 --> 00:39:40,936
Yeah.

523
00:39:58,760 --> 00:39:59,760
Barth, hold this.

524
00:40:00,280 --> 00:40:00,998
Barth, hold this.

525
00:40:01,240 --> 00:40:02,720
Stand closer together.

526
00:40:03,000 --> 00:40:04,080
Try standing side by side.

527
00:40:05,120 --> 00:40:06,400
Barth, move a little behind her.

528
00:40:06,800 --> 00:40:08,400
I want to see if the colors match.

529
00:40:08,480 --> 00:40:09,480
Okay, good.

530
00:40:09,560 --> 00:40:10,760
Oh, go ahead and unwrap it.

531
00:40:10,760 --> 00:40:12,080
This one comes with a sash too.

532
00:40:12,080 --> 00:40:13,080
Okay.

533
00:40:17,560 --> 00:40:18,560
Help me.

534
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:24,080
You can tie it tight.

535
00:40:24,840 --> 00:40:25,840
Like this?

536
00:40:27,880 --> 00:40:29,120
Are you messing with me?

537
00:40:29,680 --> 00:40:30,720
No, I'm not.

538
00:40:32,880 --> 00:40:33,880
Oh, Tanrak.

539
00:40:34,440 --> 00:40:35,440
Aren't you going in?

540
00:40:35,960 --> 00:40:36,960
Oh.

541
00:40:37,640 --> 00:40:39,880
I don't want to disturb them.

542
00:40:45,080 --> 00:40:46,080
You won't.

543
00:40:46,360 --> 00:40:47,640
They're just trying on costumes.

544
00:40:48,280 --> 00:40:49,280
Go on.

545
00:40:49,600 --> 00:40:50,600
Master.

546
00:40:52,560 --> 00:40:54,840
Please, can I be excused today?

547
00:40:57,360 --> 00:40:58,400
Are you okay?

548
00:41:00,560 --> 00:41:02,480
Well…

549
00:41:03,800 --> 00:41:05,240
I think I have a headache.

550
00:41:05,440 --> 00:41:06,760
I'm not feeling well.

551
00:41:12,920 --> 00:41:13,920
Okay.

552
00:41:14,520 --> 00:41:16,160
I'll cover music rehearsal for you today.

553
00:41:18,120 --> 00:41:19,360
You should…

554
00:41:20,160 --> 00:41:21,160
go rest.

555
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:24,000
Thank you.

556
00:41:26,640 --> 00:41:27,480
Good. Good.

557
00:41:27,480 --> 00:41:28,480
Hello, Master Win.

558
00:41:28,760 --> 00:41:30,600
Hello.

559
00:41:30,760 --> 00:41:31,600
How's it going?

560
00:41:31,760 --> 00:41:32,600
Going well.

561
00:41:32,600 --> 00:41:33,920
Barth, hold it there for now.

562
00:41:34,840 --> 00:41:35,840
Is that okay, Oh?

563
00:41:36,320 --> 00:41:37,800
Do we need to pin it?

564
00:41:37,800 --> 00:41:38,880
That's right.

565
00:41:39,360 --> 00:41:42,680
All right. Barth, try the costume on.

566
00:44:01,840 --> 00:44:03,320
Why did you finish so early today?

567
00:44:04,960 --> 00:44:05,960
I asked to leave early.

568
00:44:06,960 --> 00:44:08,000
Were you slacking off?

569
00:44:08,240 --> 00:44:09,480
You're pretty sneaky.

570
00:44:22,440 --> 00:44:23,800
Must be another power dip.

571
00:44:24,320 --> 00:44:25,320
Yeah.

572
00:44:25,840 --> 00:44:26,880
It just started raining.

573
00:44:28,240 --> 00:44:30,520
That's good. I'll sleep well tonight.

574
00:45:55,800 --> 00:45:56,800
Are you sick?

575
00:46:01,960 --> 00:46:03,000
Did you take medicine?

576
00:46:05,120 --> 00:46:06,120
Mm.

577
00:46:08,640 --> 00:46:10,000
What does “mm” mean?

578
00:46:11,520 --> 00:46:12,920
Did you take it or not?

579
00:46:14,440 --> 00:46:15,440
Do you have a fever?

580
00:46:18,960 --> 00:46:19,960
Are you warm?

581
00:46:24,720 --> 00:46:25,720
You do feel a bit warm.

582
00:46:41,600 --> 00:46:42,600
Hand me the scoop.

583
00:46:45,320 --> 00:46:46,320
Which scoop?

584
00:46:49,000 --> 00:46:50,000
This scoop?

585
00:46:51,480 --> 00:46:52,960
This isn't a normal scoop.

586
00:46:54,520 --> 00:46:57,040
This one goes Scoopy-Doopy-Doo!

587
00:47:03,560 --> 00:47:05,720
You're smiling. Are you really sick?

588
00:47:06,360 --> 00:47:07,800
Maybe your fever's gone.

589
00:47:08,720 --> 00:47:09,720
Huh?

590
00:47:10,200 --> 00:47:11,280
You don't feel feverish.

591
00:47:11,840 --> 00:47:13,200
Are you really sick?

592
00:47:15,240 --> 00:47:16,240
Let me see.

593
00:47:18,640 --> 00:47:19,640
It tickles.

594
00:47:21,600 --> 00:47:22,840
You're not that warm.

595
00:47:25,840 --> 00:47:26,880
It tickles.

596
00:47:27,080 --> 00:47:28,760
Tickles? Good.

597
00:47:29,440 --> 00:47:31,120
Stop it.

598
00:48:27,440 --> 00:48:30,000
Hey, anyone, grab a flashlight
and go check.

599
00:50:22,040 --> 00:50:25,280
Hey, if you're the last one out,
don't forget to turn off the lights.

600
00:50:54,360 --> 00:50:55,360
Tanrak.

601
00:50:57,320 --> 00:50:58,320
Tanrak.

602
00:51:00,000 --> 00:51:01,800
Tanrak, why are you running?

603
00:51:02,960 --> 00:51:03,960
I'm not running.

604
00:51:07,800 --> 00:51:09,560
You're running from yourself.

605
00:51:18,320 --> 00:51:19,320
Tanrak!

606
00:51:39,480 --> 00:51:40,480
Tanrak.

607
00:51:42,320 --> 00:51:43,440
Are you hurt?

608
00:51:49,000 --> 00:51:51,000
Can we just talk?

609
00:51:58,960 --> 00:51:59,960
Hm?

610
00:52:01,640 --> 00:52:02,920
I…

611
00:52:03,840 --> 00:52:05,160
I have nothing to say.

612
00:52:12,120 --> 00:52:16,080
You don't have things to say,
or you just don't dare say it?

613
00:52:17,520 --> 00:52:18,520
Hm?

614
00:52:24,040 --> 00:52:25,400
Don't do this, Barth.

615
00:52:31,160 --> 00:52:32,160
Tanrak.

616
00:52:34,040 --> 00:52:36,200
Whatever's on your mind, just tell me.

617
00:52:37,360 --> 00:52:38,920
Please talk to me. I'm begging you.

618
00:52:47,720 --> 00:52:49,280
I don't understand, Barth.

619
00:52:53,080 --> 00:52:54,440
I don't know anything.

620
00:52:56,440 --> 00:52:58,000
I don't even understand myself.

621
00:53:05,080 --> 00:53:06,080
You do.

622
00:53:09,880 --> 00:53:12,080
You're just scared to admit it,
aren't you?

623
00:53:18,200 --> 00:53:19,520
Just now,

624
00:53:22,160 --> 00:53:23,160
you…

625
00:53:26,240 --> 00:53:28,240
felt what I felt too, didn't you?

626
00:53:33,440 --> 00:53:34,440
Tanrak.

627
00:53:36,880 --> 00:53:39,160
Will things never be the same now?

628
00:53:44,040 --> 00:53:45,640
You know everything, don't you?

629
00:53:55,560 --> 00:53:56,560
Know what?

630
00:54:03,160 --> 00:54:04,560
That…

631
00:54:06,200 --> 00:54:08,120
I'm not God's favorite son.

632
00:54:14,040 --> 00:54:15,200
I don't understand.

633
00:54:20,600 --> 00:54:21,920
I like guys.

634
00:54:25,520 --> 00:54:26,520
Tanrak.

635
00:54:28,800 --> 00:54:29,800
I like you.

636
00:55:56,920 --> 00:55:58,280
Are you mad at me?

637
00:56:10,560 --> 00:56:12,720
I'm not God's favorite son either.

638
00:57:30,680 --> 00:57:32,840
(Next Episode)
Can you hear the voice inside your head?

639
00:57:34,000 --> 00:57:35,000
No hesitation?

640
00:57:35,200 --> 00:57:38,530
It's not like I'm unwavering.

641
00:57:39,040 --> 00:57:43,130
Some things make my heart falter.

642
00:57:43,240 --> 00:57:48,040
It's sad to have to keep it to yourself
when you like someone.

643
00:57:48,280 --> 00:57:51,440
When I'm near you,
I can't control myself at all.

644
00:57:51,680 --> 00:57:53,330
Are you happy though?

645
00:58:00,200 --> 00:58:03,770
If you could choose,
would you choose this path?

646
00:58:04,216 --> 00:58:06,330
I thought you'd take this more seriously.
